---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Business Ideas — Lucas Sommer" description="A running list of business ideas Lucas Sommer has evaluated, is exploring, or is putting out there for someone else to build.">

  <article class="ideas-page container">

    <div class="ideas-hero">
      <h1>Business Ideas</h1>
      <p class="ideas-intro">
        Ideas I've evaluated, am exploring, or am putting out there for someone else to build. Every idea here has been pressure-tested using my <a href="/resources/ideation-flow">ideation framework</a> — sized by market, priced by margin, and ranked by feasibility.
      </p>
      <p class="ideas-sub">
        Ideas are cheap. Execution is everything. If you want to build one of these, <a href="https://twitter.com/lucasbsommer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">reach out</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Filters -->
    <div class="idea-filters">
      <button class="filter-btn active" data-filter="all">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="open"><span class="filter-dot" style="background:var(--status-active-text);"></span> Open</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="exploring"><span class="filter-dot" style="background:var(--status-exploring-text);"></span> Exploring</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="building"><span class="filter-dot" style="background:var(--status-building-text);"></span> Building</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-filter="parked"><span class="filter-dot" style="background:var(--text-tertiary);"></span> Parked</button>
    </div>

    <!-- Ideas Grid -->
    <div class="ideas-grid">

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="building">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">01</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-building">Building</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">Business MCP</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">The solo founder's back-office in one Claude integration. Install once — Claude runs your business.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">AI Tooling</span>
          <span class="tag">SMB SaaS</span>
          <span class="tag">$29–$99/mo</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Solo founders and creators hate the back office — invoicing, expenses, payroll, bank reconciliation, contracts, CRM, scheduling, tax prep, legal filings, state compliance, trademarks, insurance renewals, 1099s. It's rote, repeatable, and endless.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>Claude is already the tool they want to use — MCP just makes it capable. One namespace over QuickBooks, Zoho, Gusto, Ramp, DocuSign, Google Workspace. The moat is the guided flows, not the API wrapping: <em>"end of month? here's what Claude needs to close your books in 15 min."</em> Double monetization: subscription + referral revenue from underlying tools.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Current Status</div>
            <p>Actively shaping. Sits at the intersection of Onit (product), Ad-Apt experience, and 20+ years of running multiple small businesses. Enterprise tier for bookkeepers and agencies running multiple clients through it is the second act.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="building">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">02</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-building">Building</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">Managed Agents × Onit</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">Autonomous Claude Code sessions doing real marketing work at scale. Agency-quality output at compute-cost economics.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">AI Agents</span>
          <span class="tag">MarTech</span>
          <span class="tag">$1 in / $1,500 out</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Marketing agencies charge $150/hr for work an AI agent can do in minutes: onboarding audits, campaign builds, weekly reports, creative variants, technical SEO, landing pages. Small businesses can't afford agencies but need the deliverables.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>Managed Agents = programmatic autonomous Claude sessions with full sandboxes (terminal, browser, filesystem, code execution) at $0.08/session-hour + tokens. Onit onboards a client → spins up an agent → agent runs autonomously and surfaces results. 15-min onboarding audit costs under $1 to produce. Equivalent agency value: ~$1,500.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Current Status</div>
            <p>Part of Onit's roadmap. First use cases: onboarding audits, campaign builds, weekly reporting narratives. At 1,000 clients: ~$1,000/mo in agent costs vs. millions in agency-equivalent output.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="exploring">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">03</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-exploring">Exploring</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">Live Site-Editing Chatbot</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">A widget embedded in your own site that lets you talk to your codebase and ship edits from the browser.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">Dev Tools</span>
          <span class="tag">Personal Sites</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Editing your own site — even a personal one on a modern stack — means opening a repo, running dev, editing, committing, pushing, waiting for deploy. For 90% of edits, that's more friction than the edit itself.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>A chatbot with page context (knows which page it's on), repo access (same as Claude Code), and a deploy hook. Prompt <em>"swap the hero image here"</em> → edits source → commits → deploys → live. Model selector so you can dial cost/quality. Auth-gated to the site owner.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Current Status</div>
            <p>Prototype-worthy for lucassommer.com itself. Scope-out separately: auth, model API wiring, build pipeline, deploy automation, safety guardrails. Natural fit if paired with the entrepreneurship tool suite as a "self-hosted operator."</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="open">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">04</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-open">Open</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">Geiger</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">Ambient code-activity monitor. Turns your keyboard and file changes into a productivity-tuned soundtrack.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">Desktop App</span>
          <span class="tag">Developer Tools</span>
          <span class="tag">$9 one-time or $3/mo</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Two overlapping pains. First: devs already have lofi/music playing to focus, but it's passive — no signal, no feedback. Second: agent-driven coding (Claude Code sessions, long-running scripts) leaves you wondering <em>"is it still working?"</em></p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>Listen to the factory. Your code has a rhythm — you can hear when it's running hot, cooling off, or stalled. Pings when activity stops — a subtle nudge when you've drifted, or when a long-running agent goes quiet. Replaces the passive soundtrack with a productivity-tuned one.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Who Should Build It</div>
            <p>A solo dev who loves ambient/generative music. Weekend vibe-code: Electron or Tauri, filesystem events + OS-level keystroke <em>rate</em> (no content), Web Audio oscillator or sample playback. Niche but sticky.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="open">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">05</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-open">Open</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">AR Basketball Training App</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">Smart glasses overlay a digital hoop in any space. Ball-tracked coaching on arc, form, release, follow-through.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">Consumer Hardware</span>
          <span class="tag">Sports Tech</span>
          <span class="tag">AR/CV</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Solo shooters (kids, adults, trainers) have no accountability. Real hoops require space and money. Shot-return nets solve the ball problem but give no feedback. Coaches are expensive and only see you occasionally.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>AR glasses render a digital hoop anywhere. White dots on the ball enable vision-based shot tracking. Coaching layer gives real-time feedback on shot arc, release point, follow-through, form. Target: solo shooters, youth players, trainers. Adjacent unlocks in coach-remote-analysis.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Who Should Build It</div>
            <p>A founder with sports-tech distribution + computer-vision chops or partnerships. Best paired with the AR Hoop System below as a two-pronged consumer play.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="open">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">06</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-open">Open</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">Physical Net + AR Hoop System</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">Cheap portable net catches shots and returns the ball. AR glasses render the hoop with correct physics.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">Consumer Hardware</span>
          <span class="tag">Sports Tech</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Existing solo-training options force a tradeoff: shot-return nets are convenient but have no hoop; a real hoop requires permanent installation. Neither product does both.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>Combine both. A deployable net catches shots and returns the ball; AR glasses render a virtual rim with correct physics. Counts makes and misses against the virtual hoop. Portable, no installation. Convenience of a shot-return net with the accountability of a real hoop.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Who Should Build It</div>
            <p>Hardware-plus-software founder. Bundled with idea #05 becomes a full solo-training platform: net + hoop + coaching feedback.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="idea-card" data-status="open">
        <div class="idea-top">
          <div class="idea-number">07</div>
          <span class="idea-status idea-status-open">Open</span>
        </div>
        <h2 class="idea-title">Posture-Correcting Smart Undershirt</h2>
        <p class="idea-tagline">Embedded sensors read your spine and shoulders. App nudges you when you slouch and tracks improvement over time.</p>
        <div class="idea-tags">
          <span class="tag">Wearables</span>
          <span class="tag">Consumer Health</span>
        </div>
        <div class="idea-details">
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Problem</div>
            <p>Desk work is destroying spines. Existing posture correctors are ugly, uncomfortable straps that people wear for a week and abandon. No baseline measurement, no progress feedback, no accountability past week two.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">The Opportunity</div>
            <p>Best form factor is invisible: a smart undershirt or underwear layer with embedded sensors reading spine posture, shoulder alignment, sitting pressure. Companion app tracks trends and delivers gentle nudges. Adjacent variants worth exploring: office-chair "posture seatbelt", magnet-based systems (chair + shirt magnets that detect slouch proximity).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="idea-detail">
            <div class="idea-detail-label">Who Should Build It</div>
            <p>Hardware/wearable founder with textile-sensor experience. Distribution through orthopedic and physical-therapist referrals could beat DTC on unit economics.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <div class="ideas-cta">
      <h3>Have an idea to add?</h3>
      <p>I collect ideas from conversations, problems I run into, and gaps I notice. If you want to riff on one of these — or share your own — hit me up on <a href="https://twitter.com/lucasbsommer" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitter</a>.</p>
    </div>

  </article>

  <script is:inline>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
      var buttons = document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn');
      var cards = document.querySelectorAll('.idea-card');

      buttons.forEach(function(btn) {
        btn.addEventListener('click', function() {
          buttons.forEach(function(b) { b.classList.remove('active'); });
          btn.classList.add('active');
          var filter = btn.dataset.filter;

          cards.forEach(function(card) {
            if (filter === 'all' || card.dataset.status === filter) {
              card.style.display = '';
            } else {
              card.style.display = 'none';
            }
          });
        });
      });
    });
  </script>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ideas-page {
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  /* Hero */
  .ideas-hero {
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .ideas-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -1.5px;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .ideas-intro {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ideas-sub {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  /* Filters */
  .idea-filters {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1rem 0 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .filter-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.85rem;
    font-family: inherit;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 9999px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }

  .filter-btn:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .filter-btn.active {
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #ffffff;
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  .filter-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    display: inline-block;
  }

  /* Ideas Grid */
  .ideas-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .idea-card {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .idea-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
  }

  .idea-top {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .idea-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .idea-status {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
  }

  .idea-status-open {
    background: var(--status-active-bg);
    color: var(--status-active-text);
  }

  .idea-status-exploring {
    background: var(--status-exploring-bg);
    color: var(--status-exploring-text);
  }

  .idea-status-building {
    background: var(--status-building-bg);
    color: var(--status-building-text);
  }

  .idea-status-parked {
    background: var(--surface-2);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
  }

  .idea-title {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .idea-tagline {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }

  .idea-tags {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .idea-tags .tag {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    background: var(--surface-2);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.55rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-xs);
  }

  .idea-details {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.85rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .idea-detail-label {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .idea-detail p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .idea-detail p strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  /* CTA */
  .ideas-cta {
    background: var(--surface-1);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, background-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .ideas-cta h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .ideas-cta p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* Mobile */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .ideas-hero { padding-top: 3rem; }
    .ideas-hero h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .ideas-intro { font-size: 1rem; }
    .idea-card { padding: 1.35rem; }
    .idea-title { font-size: 1.15rem; }
  }
</style>
